text: Symphony No. 3 in E-flat Major may refer to: * Symphony No. 3 (Beethoven) the Eroica * Symphony No. 3 (Dvořák) * Symphony No. 3 (Schumann), Opus 97, the Rhenish symphony * Symphony No. 3 (Shostakovich), Opus 20, The First of May * Symphony in E-flat major, Op. 11, No. 3 (Stamitz) * Symphony No. 3 (Mozart) now considered to be the work of Carl Friedrich Abel, being his Symphony No. 6 * Symphony No. 3 in E flat major, Opus 4, WK 9, by Carl Friedrich Abel * Symphony No. 3, op. 90 (1813) by Ferdinand Ries * Symphony No. 3, Op. 14 (by 1809) by Johann Wilhelm Wilms ==See also== * List of symphonies in E-flat major Category:Compositions in E-flat major
title: Symphony No. 3 in E-flat major
